n case studies of memory spaces – monuments, museums, post-war urban restoration, filmed and virtual space – in order to show the applicability and efficacy of a semiotic methodology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aHistoric sitesxInterpretive programs. 0aSemiotics. 0aSymbolism. 4aArt and Material Culture. 4aConflict and Peace. 4aHeritage Studies. 4aHistory, Art History, and Archaeology. 7aHISTORY / Military / Wars & Conflicts (Other).2bisacsh  aSemiotics, memory sites, narrativity, enunciation, risemantization.1 aDemaria, Cristina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDemaria, Cristina, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHammad, Manar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLorusso, Anna Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarrone, Gianfranco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMazzucchelli, Francesco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPanico, Mario, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPezzini, Isabella, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSalerno, Daniele, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSozzi, Paola, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVioli, Patrizia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVioli, Patrizia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102374808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 